SCHILLING v. CAR LIGHTING & POWER CO. et al. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. March 22, 1923.) No. 246. Chadbourne, Hunt & Jaeekel, of New York City (Frank Marsh, of New York City, and Carroll R. Ward, of Springfield, Mass., of counsel), for appellant. Hays, Hershfield & Wolf, of New York City (Daniel P. Hays and Edwin D. Hays, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellees.

Before ROGERS, HOUGH, and MAYER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed in open court, without costs.
